I specifically mentioned the ocean's fisheries being depleted, over 85% to be exact. Based on your misinterpretation of my Indigenous comment, I'm not surprised you misread thin as well. And no its not just salt-water species. The excess manure that's being run off into waterways is creating algae-infested pools & hypoxic dead zones which kill all kinds of fish in lakes, rivers, saltwater basins & ocean. And it's not simply the indiscriminate manner that fishing employs, but also the growing populations' demand that is causing the fish to deplete. As China and India beginning to eat more meat-based, they'll also funnel in more demand. The population will grow to 10 billion by 2050. 

